  "original_title": "Customs seize illegally imported scrap metal",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Customs seize illegally imported scrap metal",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Officers attached to the Central Intelligence Directorate (CID) of Sri Lanka Customs today seized more than 140 metric tons of scrap metal, which was restricted by the government. While attempting to smuggle the scrap metal out of the country illegally, it was taken to customs. The contents of the 20-foot container was declared to customs as natural rubber. The restricted metal was about to be shipped to India when it was intercepted based on collective intelligence and suspicion. Pix by Pradeep Pathirana"
      ],
